OL,6,FIt is not as if Huw Edwards invited
OL,7,Fthe cameras into his family life and
OL,8,Fsold the public a false image of
OL,9,Fdomestic bliss.
OL,11,FBut any accusation of inappropriate
OL,12,Fworkplace behaviour towards younger
OL,13,Fcolleagues (while far less serious
OL,14,Fthan the activities alleged in the
OL,15,Ffirst newspaper story) must also be
OL,16,Ftaken seriously ` regardless of who
OL,17,Fthe individual is.
OL,19,FIt is not unreasonable for some to
OL,20,Fask if the BBC's own news coverage
OL,21,Finadvertently fuelled the frenzy.
OL,3,CThe difficult questions arising from
OL,4,Cthe Huw Edwards story
